{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872629201,"sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41c8e8001JD4InbT3kNMIdH","messageID":"msg_d7a41b3d5001rjWQMwXaQ58FBA","sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-241658e4c2a54432899bb744427349a0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-022 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Implement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n17: \n18: **Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n19: \n20: **Target State**: \n21: - Single `kubectl-agentcube publish` command that deploys agents to Kubernetes\n22: - Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service)\n23: - Automatic image preparation via Docker push or explicit image URL\n24: - Metadata updated with deployment info, agent_id, and endpoint URLs\n25: - Namespace, replicas, and NodePort configuration support\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration logic |\n36: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `publish` Typer command with CLI options |\n37: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n38: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n39: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Image push methods (extends AR-021) |\n40: \n41: ### 2.2 PublishRuntime Methods\n42: \n43: | Method | Purpose |\n44: |--------|---------|\n45: | `publish(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n46: | `_publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via AgentCube AgentRuntime CR |\n47: | `_publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service |\n48: | `_prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Image preparation (push or URL) |\n49: | `_prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Push local Docker image to registry |\n50: | `_prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Use cloud-built image URL |\n51: | `_update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)` | Persist deployment info to metadata YAML |\n52: \n53: ### 2.3 CLI Options\n54: \n55: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n56: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n57: | `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n58: | `--version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n59: | `--image-url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n60: | `--image-username` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n61: | `--image-password` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n62: | `--description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n63: | `--region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n64: | `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n65: | `--provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n66: | `--node-port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n67: | `--replicas` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas (default: 1) |\n68: | `--namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Kubernetes namespace |\n69: | `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n70: \n71: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n72: \n73: | Item | Reason |\n74: |------|--------|\n75: | Cloud publish implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n76: | Helm chart deployment | Different deployment paradigm; future enhancement |\n77: | Auto-scaling configuration | Not specified in requirements; HPA would be separate feature |\n78: | Secret management | Beyond current scope; requires vault integration |\n79: | Multi-cluster deployment | Requires federation setup; future enhancement |\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n84: \n85: ### 3.1 新增文件\n86: \n87: ```\n88: cmd/cli/\n89: ├── agentcube/\n90: │   ├── runtime/\n91: │   │   └── publish_runtime.py     # PublishRuntime class\n92: │   ├── services/\n93: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py        # KubernetesProvider class\n94: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCubeProvider class\n95: │   │   └── docker_service.py      # (extend with push_image)\n96: │   └── cli/\n97: │       └── main.py                # publish command (addition to existing)\n98: └── tests/\n99:     ├── test_publish_runtime.py    # Unit tests for PublishRuntime\n100:     ├── test_k8s_provider.py       # Unit tests for KubernetesProvider\n101:     └── test_agentcube_provider.py # Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n105: \n106: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n107: |------------|---------|--------|\n108: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Python client for Kubernetes API; optional dependency under `[k8s]` extras |\n109: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n110: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n111: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and table output |\n112: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n113: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n114: \n115: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n116: \n117: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n118: |----------|--------------|\n119: | `invoke` command | Uses agent_endpoint from metadata for HTTP calls |\n120: | `status` command | Reads k8s_deployment info from metadata |\n121: | `pack`/`build` commands | Provide image info for publish flow |\n122: | Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent` |\n123: \n124: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n125: \n126: - **Metadata schema**: Adding `k8s_deployment` field with sub-fields (`type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`)\n127: - **Provider parameter**: New `--provider` flag changes behavior significantly\n128: - **AgentRuntime CR dependency**: Requires Volcano AgentCube CRD installed for `agentcube` provider\n129: - **Registry credentials**: Password passed via CLI flag (insecure); recommend env vars or secret files\n130: \n131: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n132: \n133: - Kubernetes client `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` reads from `~/.kube/config` by default\n134: - NodePort range must be 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n135: - AgentRuntime CR uses API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n136: - Image URL format: `{registry}/{repository}/{image}:{tag}`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n141: \n142: ### Alternative 1: Direct kubectl Execution\n143: \n144: **Approach**: Generate YAML manifests and execute `kubectl apply` via `subprocess.run()`.\n145: \n146: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n147: |--------|------------|\n148: | Pros | Familiar to K8s users; no Python SDK dependency |\n149: | Cons | No programmatic status checks; harder error parsing; platform-specific; no wait-for-ready logic |\n150: \n151: **Decision**: Rejected. Kubernetes Python SDK provides typed API, wait loops, and structured status retrieval.\n152: \n153: ### Alternative 2: Helm Chart Publishing\n154: \n155: **Approach**: Package agent as Helm chart and use `helm install` for deployment.\n156: \n157: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n158: |--------|------------|\n159: | Pros | Standard K8s packaging; templating support; versioning built-in |\n160: | Cons | Requires Helm CLI; additional complexity; not in original spec |\n161: \n162: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as alternative publishing mode in future.\n163: \n164: ### Alternative 3: Separate Push and Deploy Commands\n165: \n166: **Approach**: Split into `push-image` and `deploy` commands instead of unified `publish`.\n167: \n168: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n169: |--------|------------|\n170: | Pros | More granular control; can push without deploying |\n171: | Cons | More commands to learn; friction in typical workflow |\n172: \n173: **Decision**: Rejected. Unified `publish` command matches spec requirements and provides smoother user experience.\n174: \n175: ### Alternative 4: Docker Compose for Local Testing\n176: \n177: **Approach**: Support Docker Compose as deployment target for local development.\n178: \n179: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n180: |--------|------------|\n181: | Pros | Easy local testing; no K8s required |\n182: | Cons | Different networking model; not production-ready |\n183: \n184: **Decision**: Rejected. Focus on Kubernetes deployment per spec; local testing via `docker run` sufficient.\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## 5. Risks\n189: \n190: | Risk | Mitigation |\n191: |------|------------|\n192: | Kubernetes cluster unreachable | Load kubeconfig first; fail early with clear error message |\n193: | AgentRuntime CRD not installed | `AgentCubeProvider` checks CR existence; raises `ValueError` if not found |\n194: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url for agentcube | Validation in `_publish_cr_to_k8s` raises `ValueError` |\n195: | Image push auth failure | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles credentials; log warning on failure |\n196: | Deployment timeout | `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)` raises `TimeoutError` |\n197: | NodePort collision | K8s auto-assigns if NodePort not specified; validation for range 30000-32767 |\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n202: \n203: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n204: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace()` to create namespace if missing\n205: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for Deployment + Service creation\n206: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` with sanitization, env_vars\n207: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` with NodePort handling\n208: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout loop\n209: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` for pod/deployment status\n210: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` for cleanup\n211: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s name compliance\n212: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n213: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace()` \n214: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR\n215: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for CR name compliance\n216: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` for CR status retrieval\n217: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` orchestration entry point\n218: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n219: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n220: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` image preparation\n221: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` Docker push logic\n222: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` cloud image URL handling\n223: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` metadata persistence\n224: - [ ] Add `publish` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n225: - [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n226: - [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for publish status\n227: - [ ] Add `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n228: - [ ] Unit tests for KubernetesProvider mock K8s API\n229: - [ ] Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider mock CR API\n230: - [ ] Unit tests for image preparation logic\n231: - [ ] Integration test for full publish workflow (mocked)\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## 7. References\n236: \n237: - Spec: `changes/AR-022/spec.md`\n238: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n239: - CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: `publish` command\n240: - Deployment Spec: `deployment/spec.md` — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n241: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md` — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n242: - AR-021 — CLI build command (image preparation dependency)\n243: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n244: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n245: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-022 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Target State**: ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775872629154,"end":1775872629198}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872629203,"sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41ce36001q1aCpCk6XQ2SBJ","messageID":"msg_d7a41b3d5001rjWQMwXaQ58FBA","sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8d3e88aa5eb64aff906fc6cbbf8349fd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: [TO BE FILLED: Define scope for CLI publish command]\n16: \n17: ## Out of Scope\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Define out of scope items]\n20: \n21: ## Dependencies\n22: \n23: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n24: |------------|---------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ## Deliverables\n28: \n29: | File | Description |\n30: |------|-------------|\n31: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: \n35: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n36: \n37: ## References\n38: \n39: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n40: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n41: - AR-021 — CLI build command\n42: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n43: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define scope for CLI publish command]\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define out of scope items]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/spec.md","time":{"start":1775872629159,"end":1775872629201}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872629205,"sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41d12b0010GJYCvKzFp6p9v","messageID":"msg_d7a41b3d5001rjWQMwXaQ58FBA","sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-60e40250ea364fe2aba1eb3f97562472","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n14: - **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n15: - **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### System Context\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         User CLI                                 │\n26: │  kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./agent --provider k8s            │\n27: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n28:                               │\n29:                               ▼\n30: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n31: │                     CLI Layer (main.py)                          │\n32: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n33: │  │ Typer app.publish()                                       │   │\n34: │  │  - Parse CLI options                                      │   │\n35: │  │  - Create PublishRuntime                                  │   │\n36: │  │  - Handle errors (_handle_error)                          │   │\n37: │  │  - Display Rich Progress spinner                          │   │\n38: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n39: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40:                               │\n41:                               ▼\n42: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                    Runtime Layer                                 │\n44: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n45: │  │ PublishRuntime.publish()                                  │   │\n46: │  │  1. Load metadata (MetadataService)                       │   │\n47: │  │  2. Apply option overrides                                │   │\n48: │  │  3. Prepare image (_prepare_image_for_publishing)         │   │\n49: │  │  4. Deploy via provider                                   │   │\n50: │  │  5. Update metadata                                       │   │\n51: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n52: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n53:                               │\n54:               ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n55:               ▼               ▼               ▼\n56: ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐\n57: │ AgentCube       │ │ Kubernetes      │ │ Docker          │\n58: │ Provider        │ │ Provider        │ │ Service         │\n59: │ (CR API)        │ │ (Deployment)    │ │ (Push)          │\n60: └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n61:               │               │               │\n62:               ▼               ▼               ▼\n63: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n64: │                    Kubernetes Cluster                            │\n65: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐     │\n66: │  │ AgentRuntime CR  │  │ Deployment + NodePort Service    │     │\n67: │  │ (agentcube)      │  │ (k8s)                            │     │\n68: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────────┘     │\n69: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Component Diagram\n73: \n74: ```\n75: PublishRuntime\n76: ├── MetadataService (load/save metadata)\n77: ├── DockerService (push_image, login, tag)\n78: ├── Provider Selection\n79: │   ├── AgentCubeProvider (provider=\"agentcube\")\n80: │   │   ├── CustomObjectsApi (CR create/patch)\n81: │   │   ├── CoreV1Api (namespace)\n82: │   │   └── _sanitize_name()\n83: │   │   └── _ensure_namespace()\n84: │   └── KubernetesProvider (provider=\"k8s\")\n85: │       ├── AppsV1Api (Deployment)\n86: │       ├── CoreV1Api (Service, Namespace)\n87: │       ├── _create_deployment()\n88: │       ├── _create_service()\n89: │       ├── wait_for_deployment_ready()\n90: │       └── _sanitize_name()\n91: └── _update_publish_metadata()\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Data Structures\n97: \n98: ### AgentMetadata Extensions (Pydantic BaseModel)\n99: \n100: ```python\n101: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n102:     agent_name: str\n103:     description: Optional[str] = None\n104:     language: str = \"python\"\n105:     entrypoint: str\n106:     port: int = 8080\n107:     build_mode: str = \"local\"\n108:     region: Optional[str] = None\n109:     version: Optional[str] = None\n110:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n111:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n112:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n113:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n114:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n115:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n116:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n117:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n118:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n119:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n120:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n121:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None       # NEW: Assigned by AgentCube\n122:     session_id: Optional[str] = None\n123:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # NEW: Deployment info\n124: \n125:     @validator(\"language\")\n126:     def validate_language(cls, v):\n127:         allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n128:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n129:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n130:         return v.lower()\n131: \n132:     @validator(\"build_mode\")\n133:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v):\n134:         allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n135:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n136:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n137:         return v.lower()\n138: \n139:     @validator(\"port\")\n140:     def validate_port(cls, v):\n141:         if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n142:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n143:         return v\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ### k8s_deployment Field Structure\n147: \n148: ```python\n149: k8s_deployment: Dict[str, Any] = {\n150:     \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\" | \"Deployment\",\n151:     \"deployment_name\": str,\n152:     \"service_name\": str,           # k8s provider only\n153:     \"namespace\": str,\n154:     \"replicas\": int,\n155:     \"node_port\": int,              # k8s provider only\n156:     \"service_url\": str,            # k8s provider only: \"http://localhost:{node_port}\"\n157:     \"agent_id\": str,               # agentcube provider only\n158:     \"status\": \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"error\",\n159:     \"error\": Optional[str],        # Set on failure\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### PublishOptions (Internal)\n164: \n165: ```python\n166: @dataclass\n167: class PublishOptions:\n168:     workspace: Path\n169:     version: Optional[str] = None\n170:     image_url: Optional[str] = None\n171:     image_username: Optional[str] = None\n172:     image_password: Optional[str] = None\n173:     description: Optional[str] = None\n174:     region: Optional[str] = None\n175:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None\n176:     provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n177:     node_port: Optional[int] = None\n178:     replicas: Optional[int] = None\n179:     namespace: Optional[str] = None\n180:     verbose: bool = False\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## API Contracts\n186: \n187: ### Typer Command Interface\n188: \n189: ```python\n190: @app.command()\n191: def publish(\n192:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", \n193:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n194:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\",\n195:         help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n196:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\",\n197:         help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n198:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\",\n199:         help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n200:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\",\n201:         help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n202:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\",\n203:         help=\"Agent description\"),\n204:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\",\n205:         help=\"Deployment region\"),\n206:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n207:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n208:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\",\n209:         help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n210:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\",\n211:         help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n212:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\",\n213:         help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n214:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\",\n215:         help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n216:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\",\n217:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n218: ) -> None:\n219:     \"\"\"Deploy agent to Kubernetes cluster.\"\"\"\n220:     try:\n221:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n222:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n223:         options = {\n224:             \"version\": version,\n225:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n226:             \"image_username\": image_username,\n227:             \"image_password\": image_password,\n228:             \"description\": description,\n229:             \"region\": region,\n230:             \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n231:             \"node_port\": node_port,\n232:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n233:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n234:         }\n235:         with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\")) as progress:\n236:             task = progress.add_task(\"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\", total=None)\n237:             result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)\n238:             progress.remove_task(task)\n239:         \n240:         console.print(f\"[green]Successfully published agent![/green]\")\n241:         console.print(f\"  Agent Name: {result['agent_name']}\")\n242:         console.print(f\"  Agent ID: {result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}\")\n243:         console.print(f\"  Endpoint: {result['agent_endpoint']}\")\n244:         console.print(f\"  Deployment Type: {result['deployment_type']}\")\n245:         console.print(f\"  Namespace: {result['namespace']}\")\n246:         \n247:     except Exception as e:\n248:         _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### PublishRuntime Contract\n252: \n253: ```python\n254: class PublishRuntime:\n255:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n256:         self.verbose = verbose\n257:         self.provider = provider\n258:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n259:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n260:         \n261:         if provider == \"k8s\":\n262:             self.k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\n263:         elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n264:             self.agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\n265:         else:\n266:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n267: \n268:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n269:         \"\"\"\n270:         Orchestrates the publish workflow.\n271:         \n272:         Returns:\n273:             Dict containing agent_name, agent_id, agent_endpoint, deployment_type, namespace, k8s_deployment\n274:         \"\"\"\n275:         ...\n276: \n277:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n278:         \"\"\"Deploy via AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n279:         ...\n280: \n281:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n282:         \"\"\"Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n283:         ...\n284: \n285:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n286:         \"\"\"Return image URL ready for deployment.\"\"\"\n287:         ...\n288: \n289:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n290:         \"\"\"Push local Docker image to registry.\"\"\"\n291:         ...\n292: \n293:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n294:         \"\"\"Use cloud-built image URL.\"\"\"\n295:         ...\n296: \n297:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n298:         \"\"\"Persist deployment info to metadata YAML.\"\"\"\n299:         ...\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### AgentCubeProvider Contract\n303: \n304: ```python\n305: class AgentCubeProvider:\n306:     CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n307:     CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n308:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n309:     \n310:     def __init__(\n311:         self,\n312:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n313:         verbose: bool = False,\n314:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n315:     ) -> None:\n316:         self.namespace = namespace\n317:         self.verbose = verbose\n318:         \n319:         if kubeconfig:\n320:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n321:         else:\n322:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n323:         \n324:         self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()\n325:         self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n326: \n327:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n328:         self,\n329:         agent_name: str,\n330:         image_url: str,\n331:         port: int,\n332:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n333:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n334:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n335:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n336:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n337:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n338:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n339:         \"\"\"Create or patch AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n340:         ...\n341: \n342:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n343:         \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n344:         ...\n345: \n346:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n347:         \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n348:         ...\n349: \n350:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n351:         \"\"\"Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status.\"\"\"\n352:         ...\n353: ```\n354: \n355: ### KubernetesProvider Contract\n356: \n357: ```python\n358: class KubernetesProvider:\n359:     NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000\n360:     NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767\n361:     DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n362:     POLL_INTERVAL = 2\n363:     \n364:     def __init__(\n365:         self,\n366:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n367:         verbose: bool = False,\n368:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n369:     ) -> None:\n370:         self.namespace = namespace\n371:         self.verbose = verbose\n372:         \n373:         if kubeconfig:\n374:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n375:         else:\n376:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n377:         \n378:         self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()\n379:         self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n380: \n381:     def deploy_agent(\n382:         self,\n383:         agent_name: str,\n384:         image_url: str,\n385:         port: int,\n386:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n387:         replicas: int = 1,\n388:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n389:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n390:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n391:         \"\"\"Create Deployment + NodePort Service and wait for ready.\"\"\"\n392:         ...\n393: \n394:     def _create_deployment(\n395:         self,\n396:         name: str,\n397:         image_url: str,\n398:         port: int,\n399:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n400:         replicas: int,\n401:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n402:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n403:         \"\"\"Create Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n404:         ...\n405: \n406:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n407:         \"\"\"Create NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n408:         ...\n409: \n410:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n411:         \"\"\"Poll deployment status until ready or timeout.\"\"\"\n412:         ...\n413: \n414:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n415:         \"\"\"Get Deployment and Service status.\"\"\"\n416:         ...\n417: \n418:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n419:         \"\"\"Delete Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n420:         ...\n421: \n422:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n423:         \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n424:         ...\n425: \n426:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n427:         \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n428:         ...\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ---\n432: \n433: ## Error Handling\n434: \n435: ### Error Categories\n436: \n437: | Category | Exception Type | Message Pattern | Recovery |\n438: |----------|----------------|-----------------|----------|\n439: | Metadata Missing | `ValueError` | `Missing required field: {field} in agent_metadata.yaml` | User must add field |\n440: | Provider Invalid | `ValueError` | `Invalid provider: {value}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'` | Use valid provider |\n441: | Image URL Missing | `ValueError` | `--image-url is required for local build mode` | Provide image URL |\n442: | Router URL Missing | `ValueError` | `router_url is required for agentcube provider in agent_metadata.yaml` | Add router_url |\n443: | Workload Manager Missing | `ValueError` | `workload_manager_url is required for agentcube provider` | Add workload_manager_url |\n444: | NodePort Invalid | `ValueError` | `NodePort must be in range 30000-32767` | Use valid NodePort |\n445: | Docker Unavailable | `RuntimeError` | `Docker is not available or not running` | Start Docker |\n446: | Docker Push Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Failed to push image: {details}` | Check credentials |\n447: | K8s Unreachable | `RuntimeError` | `Kubernetes cluster is unreachable` | Check kubeconfig |\n448: | CRD Not Found | `ValueError` | `AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Install Volcano AgentCube CRDs` | Install CRDs |\n449: | Deployment Timeout | `TimeoutError` | `Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s` | Check pod logs |\n450: | Registry Auth Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Registry authentication failed: {details}` | Check credentials |\n451: \n452: ### Error Handling Pattern\n453: \n454: ```python\n455: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n456:     \"\"\"Print error and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n457:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n458:     if verbose:\n459:         console.print_exception()\n460:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n461: ```\n462: \n463: ### Metadata Error Recording\n464: \n465: ```python\n466: def _record_error_in_metadata(workspace_path: Path, error_msg: str) -> None:\n467:     \"\"\"Record error in metadata before raising exception.\"\"\"\n468:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n469:     metadata.k8s_deployment = {\n470:         \"status\": \"error\",\n471:         \"error\": error_msg,\n472:     }\n473:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n474: ```\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## Testing Strategy\n479: \n480: ### Unit Tests\n481: \n482: | Test File | Coverage |\n483: |-----------|----------|\n484: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | PublishRuntime orchestration, option overrides, provider selection |\n485: | `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | KubernetesProvider methods with mocked K8s API |\n486: | `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | AgentCubeProvider CR creation/patch with mocked API |\n487: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | push_image, login, tag methods |\n488: \n489: ### Mock Strategy\n490: \n491: ```python\n492: # Kubernetes API Mock\n493: @pytest.fixture\n494: def mock_k8s_api():\n495:     with patch(\"kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api\") as mock_apps:\n496:         with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\") as mock_core:\n497:             mock_apps.return_value.create_deployment.return_value = ...\n498:             mock_core.return_value.create_namespaced_service.return_value = ...\n499:             yield mock_apps, mock_core\n500: \n501: # AgentRuntime CR Mock\n502: @pytest.fixture\n503: def mock_custom_api():\n504:     with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\") as mock_custom:\n505:         mock_custom.return_value.create_custom_object.return_value = {\n506:             \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test-agent\"},\n507:             \"status\": {\"agentEndpoint\": \"http://test\"},\n508:         }\n509:         yield mock_custom\n510: \n511: # Docker Mock\n512: @pytest.fixture\n513: def mock_docker():\n514:     with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock_client:\n515:         mock_client.return_value.images.push.return_value = [...]\n516:         yield mock_client\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ### Test Cases\n520: \n521: | Test Case | Scenario |\n522: |-----------|----------|\n523: | `test_publish_agentcube_success` | Valid metadata, agentcube provider, CR created |\n524: | `test_publish_k8s_success` | Valid metadata, k8s provider, Deployment + Service created |\n525: | `test_publish_missing_router_url` | agentcube provider without router_url raises ValueError |\n526: | `test_publish_missing_workload_manager` | agentcube provider without workload_manager_url raises ValueError |\n527: | `test_publish_invalid_provider` | Invalid provider raises ValueError |\n528: | `test_publish_image_url_required_local` | Local build mode without image_url raises ValueError |\n529: | `test_publish_node_port_out_of_range` | NodePort outside 30000-32767 raises ValueError |\n530: | `test_publish_deployment_timeout` | Deployment not ready after 120s raises TimeoutError |\n531: | `test_publish_metadata_update` | Metadata saved with agent_id and k8s_deployment |\n532: | `test_publish_error_metadata_update` | Error recorded in metadata before exception |\n533: | `test_k8s_provider_sanitize_name` | Name sanitized to DNS-compliant format |\n534: | `test_agentcube_provider_sanitize_name` | CR name sanitized |\n535: | `test_agentcube_provider_patch_existing_cr` | Patch instead of create for existing CR |\n536: | `test_docker_push_with_credentials` | Login + push with username/password |\n537: | `test_docker_push_without_credentials` | Push without login (pre-authenticated) |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## File Structure\n542: \n543: ```\n544: cmd/cli/\n545: ├── agentcube/\n546: │   ├── __init__.py                    # Package exports\n547: │   ├── cli/\n548: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n549: │   │   └── main.py                    # Typer app + publish command\n550: │   ├── runtime/\n551: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n552: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # (AR-020)\n553: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py           # (AR-021)\n554: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # NEW: PublishRuntime\n555: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # (AR-023)\n556: │   │   └── status_runtime.py          # (AR-024)\n557: │   ├── services/\n558: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n559: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py        # Load/save metadata\n560: │   │   ├── docker_service.py          # EXTEND: push_image, login, tag\n561: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # NEW: KubernetesProvider\n562: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # NEW: AgentCubeProvider\n563: │   └── models/\n564: │       ├── __init__.py\n565: │       └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions\n566: ├── tests/\n567: │   ├── test_publish_runtime.py        # NEW\n568: │   ├── test_k8s_provider.py           # NEW\n569: │   ├── test_agentcube_provider.py     # NEW\n570: │   └── test_docker_service.py         # EXTEND\n571: ├── pyproject.toml                     # Dependencies\n572: └── examples/\n573:     └── hello-agent/\n574:         ├── main.py\n575:         └── agent_metadata.yaml        # Example metadata\n576: ```\n577: \n578: ---\n579: \n580: ## Dependencies\n581: \n582: ### Runtime Dependencies\n583: \n584: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n585: |---------|---------|---------|\n586: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n587: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n588: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n589: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n590: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client (optional `[k8s]` extras) |\n591: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n592: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n593: | `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n594: \n595: ### pyproject.toml Optional Dependencies\n596: \n597: ```toml\n598: [project.optional-dependencies]\n599: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n600: dev = [\n601:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n602:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n603:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n604:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n605:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n606:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n607:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n608: ]\n609: test = [\n610:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n611:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n612:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n613:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n614:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n615: ]\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ---\n619: \n620: ## Implementation Notes\n621: \n622: ### Constants\n623: \n624: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n625: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n626: | `CR_GROUP` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n627: | `CR_VERSION` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n628: | `CR_PLURAL` | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n629: | `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default session timeout |\n630: | `MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default max session duration |\n631: | `DEFAULT_SECRET` | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default imagePullSecret |\n632: | `NODE_PORT_MIN` | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n633: | `NODE_PORT_MAX` | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n634: | `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Deployment readiness timeout |\n635: | `POLL_INTERVAL` | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Status poll interval (seconds) |\n636: \n637: ### AgentRuntime CR Template\n638: \n639: ```python\n640: cr_body = {\n641:     \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.CR_GROUP}/{self.CR_VERSION}\",\n642:     \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n643:     \"metadata\": {\n644:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n645:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n646:     },\n647:     \"spec\": {\n648:         \"image\": image_url,\n649:         \"port\": port,\n650:         \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n651:         \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n652:         \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n653:         \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n654:         \"env\": [\n655:             {\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url},\n656:             {\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url},\n657:         ],\n658:         \"readinessProbe\": {\n659:             \"httpGet\": {\n660:                 \"path\": readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n661:                 \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n662:             },\n663:         },\n664:     },\n665: }\n666: ```\n667: \n668: ### Kubernetes Deployment Template\n669: \n670: ```python\n671: deployment_body = {\n672:     \"apiVersion\": \"apps/v1\",\n673:     \"kind\": \"Deployment\",\n674:     \"metadata\": {\n675:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n676:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n677:         \"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n678:     },\n679:     \"spec\": {\n680:         \"replicas\": replicas,\n681:         \"selector\": {\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n682:         \"template\": {\n683:             \"metadata\": {\"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n684:             \"spec\": {\n685:                 \"containers\": [{\n686:                     \"name\": sanitized_name,\n687:                     \"image\": image_url,\n688:                     \"ports\": [{\"containerPort\": port}],\n689:                     \"env\": [{\"name\": k, \"value\": v} for k, v in (env_vars or {}).items()],\n690:                 }],\n691:             },\n692:         },\n693:     },\n694: }\n695: ```\n696: \n697: ### NodePort Service Template\n698: \n699: ```python\n700: service_body = {\n701:     \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n702:     \"kind\": \"Service\",\n703:     \"metadata\": {\n704:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n705:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n706:     },\n707:     \"spec\": {\n708:         \"type\": \"NodePort\",\n709:         \"selector\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n710:         \"ports\": [{\n711:             \"port\": port,\n712:             \"targetPort\": port,\n713:             \"nodePort\": node_port,  # Optional, K8s auto-assigns if None\n714:         }],\n715:     },\n716: }\n717: ```\n718: \n719: ### Name Sanitization Algorithm\n720: \n721: ```python\n722: def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n723:     \"\"\"\n724:     Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\n725:     Rules:\n726:     - Lowercase only\n727:     - Replace non-alphanumeric with '-'\n728:     - Truncate to 63 characters\n729:     - Remove leading/trailing '-'\n730:     \"\"\"\n731:     sanitized = name.lower()\n732:     sanitized = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", sanitized)\n733:     sanitized = re.sub(r\"-+\", \"-\", sanitized)\n734:     sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n735:     return sanitized[:63]\n736: ```\n737: \n738: ### Wait for Deployment Ready Algorithm\n739: \n740: ```python\n741: def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n742:     start = time.time()\n743:     while time.time() - start < timeout:\n744:         deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n745:         if deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas:\n746:             return\n747:         time.sleep(self.POLL_INTERVAL)\n748:     raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s\")\n749: ```\n750: \n751: ---\n752: \n753: ## References\n754: \n755: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n756: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (publish command requirements)\n757: - deployment/spec.md — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n758: - python-sdk/spec.md — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n759: - AR-021 — CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n760: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n761: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n762: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n763: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n764: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n765: - Volcano AgentCube CRD: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n\n(End of file - total 765 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n- **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n- **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775872629162,"end":1775872629203}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872629208,"sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41d55c001MzIKcaE75AiW55","messageID":"msg_d7a41b3d5001rjWQMwXaQ58FBA","sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-958ede8b4a0646e59667a42a95f57953","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Publish Command Entry Point\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a `publish` subcommand via Typer application to deploy agents to Kubernetes with provider selection.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without specifying any options\n24: - **WHEN** the command is invoked\n25: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n26:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n27:   - `version` = `None` (`--version`, type `Optional[str]`)\n28:   - `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`, type `Optional[str]`)\n29:   - `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`, type `Optional[str]`)\n30:   - `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`, type `Optional[str]`)\n31:   - `description` = `None` (`--description`, type `Optional[str]`)\n32:   - `region` = `None` (`--region`, type `Optional[str]`)\n33:   - `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, type `Optional[str]`)\n34:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, type `str`)\n35:   - `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, type `Optional[int]`)\n36:   - `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`, type `Optional[int]`)\n37:   - `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`, type `Optional[str]`)\n38:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, type `bool`)\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Successful Publish with AgentCube Provider\n41: \n42: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with metadata containing `agent_name`, `image`, `router_url`, and `workload_manager_url`\n43: - **WHEN** `publish` completes with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n44: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n45:   - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n46:   - Print success message including `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, and deployment type\n47:   - Exit with code `0`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Successful Publish with Kubernetes Provider\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with metadata containing `agent_name`, `image`, and Kubernetes cluster accessible\n52: - **WHEN** `publish` completes with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n53: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n54:   - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n55:   - Print success message including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n56:   - Exit with code `0`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Publish Failure Handling with Verbose\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n61: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n62: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n63:   - Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red via Rich\n64:   - Print the full traceback\n65:   - Exit with code `1`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Publish Failure Handling without Verbose\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n70: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n71: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n72:   - Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red via Rich\n73:   - Exit with code `1` without printing traceback\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: PublishRuntime Initialization\n78: \n79: The system SHALL construct `PublishRuntime` with provider selection.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime Constructor Default Provider\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=False)` is constructed\n84: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n85: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n86:   - Set `provider` to `\"agentcube\"` (default)\n87:   - Initialize `MetadataService` for metadata operations\n88:   - Initialize `DockerService` for image push operations\n89:   - Store the `verbose` flag for logging control\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime Constructor Explicit Provider\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"k8s\")` is constructed\n94: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n95: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n96:   - Set `provider` to `\"k8s\"`\n97:   - Initialize `KubernetesProvider` with default namespace `\"default\"`\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: PublishRuntime.publish Orchestration\n102: \n103: The system SHALL orchestrate the publish workflow with validation, image preparation, deployment, and metadata update.\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Load Metadata from Workspace\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n108: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(workspace_path, **options)` runs\n109: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n110:   - Call `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n111:   - Validate metadata has required `agent_name` and `image` fields\n112:   - Raise `ValueError` if metadata is missing required fields\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Apply CLI Option Overrides\n115: \n116: - **GIVEN** metadata loaded from workspace\n117: - **WHEN** CLI options are provided\n118: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n119:   - Override `metadata.version` if `--version` is provided\n120:   - Override `metadata.description` if `--description` is provided\n121:   - Override `metadata.region` if `--region` is provided\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Provider Selection Branching\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** `provider` option is set\n126: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` determines deployment method\n127: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n128:   - Call `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` if `provider == \"agentcube\"`\n129:   - Call `_publish_k8s()` if `provider == \"k8s\"`\n130:   - Raise `ValueError` if `provider` is neither `\"agentcube\"` nor `\"k8s\"`\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Image Preparation\n135: \n136: The system SHALL prepare the container image for deployment via Docker push or explicit URL.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Prepare Image for Publishing\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `build_mode`\n141: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` runs\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n143:   - Call `_prepare_local_image()` if `build_mode == \"local\"`\n144:   - Call `_prepare_cloud_image()` if `build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Prepare Local Image with Registry\n147: \n148: - **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"local\"` and `image_url` is provided\n149: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` runs\n150: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n151:   - Call `DockerService.push_image()` with registry URL and credentials\n152:   - Return the pushed image URL `{registry_url}/{agent_name}:{version}`\n153:   - Raise `RuntimeError` if Docker push fails\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Prepare Local Image Missing URL\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"local\"` and `image_url` is not provided\n158: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` runs\n159: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `--image-url` is required for local build mode\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Prepare Cloud Image URL\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"cloud\"` and `cloud_provider` is provided\n164: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n165: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n166:   - Return the image URL from `metadata.image` field\n167:   - Log warning if cloud publish is not fully implemented\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n172: \n173: The system SHALL validate required fields before deploying via AgentCube provider.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Validate Router URL\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"` and `metadata.router_url` is `None` or empty\n178: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n179: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager URL\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"` and `metadata.workload_manager_url` is `None` or empty\n184: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n185: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Validate Readiness Probe Fields\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"`\n190: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` runs\n191: - **THEN** the system SHALL use:\n192:   - `metadata.readiness_probe_path` or default `\"/health\"`\n193:   - `metadata.readiness_probe_port` or `metadata.port`\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: AgentCube Provider Deployment\n198: \n199: The system SHALL deploy via AgentRuntime CR to Kubernetes.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: AgentCubeProvider Initialization\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=False)`\n204: - **WHEN** the provider is constructed\n205: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n206:   - Load kubeconfig via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()`\n207:   - Initialize CustomObjectApi client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n208:   - Set namespace to `\"default\"` or provided value\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Ensure Namespace Exists\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized\n213: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n214: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n215:   - Check if namespace exists via `CoreV1Api.read_namespace()`\n216:   - Create namespace if it does not exist\n217:   - Log creation in verbose mode\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n220: \n221: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` is called\n222: - **WHEN** the CR is created\n223: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n224:   - Create CustomObject with `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n225:   - Set CR name via `_sanitize_name(agent_name)` (lowercase, DNS compliant)\n226:   - Set `spec.image` to image URL\n227:   - Set `spec.port` to metadata port\n228:   - Set `spec.sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"`\n229:   - Set `spec.maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n230:   - Set `spec.imagePullSecrets` to `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n231:   - Embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` in `spec.env` when provided\n232:   - Return result dict with `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `deployment_name`\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Sanitize Name for CR\n235: \n236: - **GIVEN** `agent_name` contains special characters or uppercase\n237: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name(agent_name)` runs\n238: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n239:   - Convert to lowercase\n240:   - Replace invalid characters with `-`\n241:   - Truncate to 63 characters if exceeds Kubernetes name limit\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Patch Existing AgentRuntime CR\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR with the same name already exists\n246: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime()` runs\n247: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n248:   - Use `patch_custom_object` instead of `create_custom_object`\n249:   - Update image, port, and environment variables\n250:   - Return updated CR info\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Provider Deployment\n255: \n256: The system SHALL deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service.\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: KubernetesProvider Initialization\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=False)`\n261: - **WHEN** the provider is constructed\n262: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n263:   - Load kubeconfig via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()`\n264:   - Initialize `AppsV1Api` for Deployment management\n265:   - Initialize `CoreV1Api` for Service and Namespace management\n266:   - Set namespace to `\"default\"` or provided value\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Deploy Agent with Deployment and Service\n269: \n270: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` is called\n271: - **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n273:   - Call `_create_deployment()` to create Deployment\n274:   - Call `_create_service()` to create NodePort Service\n275:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout `120`\n276:   - Return result dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Create Deployment\n279: \n280: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` is called\n281: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n282: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n283:   - Set Deployment name via `_sanitize_name(agent_name)`\n284:   - Set `spec.replicas` to provided value or `1`\n285:   - Set container image, port, and optional entrypoint command\n286:   - Add `env_vars` to container spec if provided\n287:   - Set `selector.matchLabels` and `template.metadata.labels` to `{\"app\": sanitized_name}`\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Create NodePort Service\n290: \n291: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` is called\n292: - **WHEN** Service is created\n293: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n294:   - Set Service type to `NodePort`\n295:   - Set port to `metadata.port`\n296:   - Set `nodePort` to provided value if within range `30000-32767`\n297:   - Raise `ValueError` if `node_port` is outside valid range\n298:   - Allow Kubernetes to auto-assign NodePort if `node_port` is `None`\n299: \n300: #### Scenario: Wait for Deployment Ready\n301: \n302: - **GIVEN** deployment is created\n303: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` runs\n304: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n305:   - Poll deployment status every 2 seconds\n306:   - Check `status.availableReplicas == spec.replicas`\n307:   - Raise `TimeoutError` if timeout exceeded before ready\n308:   - Log progress in verbose mode\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: Deployment Readiness Failure\n311: \n312: - **GIVEN** deployment fails to become ready within timeout\n313: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready()` exceeds timeout\n314: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n315:   - Raise `RuntimeError` with deployment failure message\n316:   - Record error in metadata before raising\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: Delete Agent Resources\n319: \n320: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n321: - **WHEN** deletion proceeds\n322: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n323:   - Delete Deployment via `delete_deployment()`\n324:   - Delete Service via `delete_service()`\n325:   - Ignore 404 errors for individual resources\n326:   - Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}`\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: Metadata Update After Publish\n331: \n332: The system SHALL persist deployment information to metadata YAML.\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Update Publish Metadata\n335: \n336: - **GIVEN** deployment completes successfully\n337: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` runs\n338: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n339:   - Update `metadata.agent_id` from deployment result\n340:   - Update `metadata.agent_endpoint` from deployment result\n341:   - Update `metadata.k8s_deployment` with deployment info dict\n342:   - Save metadata via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: k8s_deployment Field Structure\n345: \n346: - **GIVEN** metadata is updated after publish\n347: - **WHEN** `k8s_deployment` field is set\n348: - **THEN** the field SHALL contain:\n349:   - `type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` for agentcube provider or `\"Deployment\"` for k8s provider\n350:   - `deployment_name`: sanitized deployment name\n351:   - `service_name`: sanitized service name (k8s provider)\n352:   - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n353:   - `replicas`: replica count\n354:   - `node_port`: NodePort number (k8s provider)\n355:   - `service_url`: `http://localhost:{node_port}` (k8s provider)\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Record Error in Metadata on Failure\n358: \n359: - **GIVEN** deployment fails\n360: - **WHEN** error is recorded before raising\n361: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n362:   - Set `k8s_deployment.error` to error message\n363:   - Set `k8s_deployment.status` to `\"error\"`\n364:   - Save metadata before raising exception\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ### Requirement: Namespace Configuration\n369: \n370: The system SHALL support namespace configuration via CLI option.\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: Use Specified Namespace\n373: \n374: - **GIVEN** `--namespace my-namespace` is provided\n375: - **WHEN** provider is initialized\n376: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n377:   - Pass namespace to `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider`\n378:   - Create resources in specified namespace\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Default Namespace\n381: \n382: - **GIVEN** `--namespace` is not provided\n383: - **WHEN** provider is initialized\n384: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n385:   - Use namespace from `metadata.k8s_deployment.namespace` if exists\n386:   - Use `\"default\"` as fallback\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Replicas Configuration\n391: \n392: The system SHALL support replica count configuration.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Use Specified Replicas\n395: \n396: - **GIVEN** `--replicas 3` is provided\n397: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Deployment is created\n398: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be set to `3`\n399: \n400: #### Scenario: Default Replicas\n401: \n402: - **GIVEN** `--replicas` is not provided\n403: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Deployment is created\n404: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL default to `1`\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ### Requirement: NodePort Configuration\n409: \n410: The system SHALL support NodePort specification for Kubernetes Service.\n411: \n412: #### Scenario: Use Specified NodePort\n413: \n414: - **GIVEN** `--node-port 30080` is provided\n415: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Service is created\n416: - **THEN** `spec.ports[0].nodePort` SHALL be set to `30080`\n417: \n418: #### Scenario: NodePort Range Validation\n419: \n420: - **GIVEN** `--node-port 20000` is provided (outside range)\n421: - **WHEN** `_create_service()` validates\n422: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be in range `30000-32767`\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Auto-assign NodePort\n425: \n426: - **GIVEN** `--node-port` is not provided\n427: - **WHEN** Kubernetes Service is created\n428: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL auto-assign a NodePort within valid range\n429: \n430: ---\n431: \n432: ### Requirement: Version Override\n433: \n434: The system SHALL support version string override.\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Override Version via CLI\n437: \n438: - **GIVEN** `--version v1.0.0` is provided\n439: - **WHEN** metadata is updated before publish\n440: - **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL be set to `\"v1.0.0\"`\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: Use Metadata Version\n443: \n444: - **GIVEN** `--version` is not provided and metadata has `version`\n445: - **WHEN** image is tagged or pushed\n446: - **THEN** the system SHALL use existing `metadata.version`\n447: \n448: ---\n449: \n450: ### Requirement: Registry Credentials\n451: \n452: The system SHALL support registry authentication for image push.\n453: \n454: #### Scenario: Push Image with Credentials\n455: \n456: - **GIVEN** `--image-username` and `--image-password` are provided\n457: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` runs\n458: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n459:   - Call `_docker_login_sdk()` with credentials\n460:   - Login to registry before push\n461:   - Stream push logs in verbose mode\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: Push Image without Credentials\n464: \n465: - **GIVEN** `--image-username` and `--image-password` are not provided\n466: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` runs\n467: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n468:   - Skip login step\n469:   - Attempt push assuming pre-authenticated Docker client\n470:   - Log warning if push fails due to auth\n471: \n472: #### Scenario: Docker Login SDK Method\n473: \n474: - **GIVEN** `DockerService._docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` is called\n475: - **WHEN** login executes\n476: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n477:   - Use `docker.from_env().login()` method\n478:   - Handle login failure gracefully\n479:   - Log success/failure message\n480: \n481: ---\n482: \n483: ### Requirement: Image Tag and Retag\n484: \n485: The system SHALL handle image tagging and retagging for registry push.\n486: \n487: #### Scenario: Tag Image for Registry\n488: \n489: - **GIVEN** local image `{agent_name}:latest`\n490: - **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` prepares for push\n491: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n492:   - Tag image as `{registry_url}/{agent_name}:{version}`\n493:   - Call `_tag_image_sdk()` for Docker SDK tagging\n494: \n495: #### Scenario: Tag Image SDK Method\n496: \n497: - **GIVEN** `DockerService._tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image)` is called\n498: - **WHEN** tagging executes\n499: - **THEN** `docker_client.images.get(source_image).tag(target_image)` SHALL be called\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ### Requirement: Error Handling Patterns\n504: \n505: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate messages and metadata updates.\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: Kubernetes Cluster Unreachable\n508: \n509: - **GIVEN** kubeconfig cannot connect to cluster\n510: - **WHEN** provider initialization runs\n511: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with message indicating cluster unreachable\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD Not Installed\n514: \n515: - **GIVEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` CRD does not exist\n516: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` attempts CR creation\n517: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n518:   - Catch API exception for CRD not found\n519:   - Raise `ValueError` indicating AgentCube CRD must be installed\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: Image Push Auth Failure\n522: \n523: - **GIVEN** registry credentials are invalid\n524: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` attempts push\n525: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n526:   - Catch Docker API exception\n527:   - Raise `RuntimeError` with auth failure message\n528:   - Log detailed error in verbose mode\n529: \n530: ---\n531: \n532: ### Requirement: Verbose Logging\n533: \n534: The system SHALL enable detailed logging when `--verbose` is passed.\n535: \n536: #### Scenario: Verbose Logging During Publish\n537: \n538: - **GIVEN** `--verbose` is passed to publish command\n539: - **WHEN** publish runs\n540: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n541:   - Log each step: metadata loading, image preparation, deployment\n542:   - Log Kubernetes API calls and responses\n543:   - Log Docker push progress\n544:   - Include intermediate results in logs\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ### Requirement: Progress Indicator During Publish\n549: \n550: The system SHALL display a progress spinner during publish operations.\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: Rich Progress Spinner Display\n553: \n554: - **GIVEN** the publish command is executing\n555: - **WHEN** operations like image push and deployment run\n556: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner with descriptive text (e.g., \"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\")\n557: \n558: ---\n559: \n560: ### Requirement: Publish Result Structure\n561: \n562: The system SHALL return a structured result from `PublishRuntime.publish`.\n563: \n564: #### Scenario: Return Publish Result Dictionary\n565: \n566: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` completes successfully\n567: - **WHEN** the method returns\n568: - **THEN** the result SHALL be a `Dict[str, Any]` containing:\n569:   - `agent_name`: the resolved agent name\n570:   - `agent_id`: assigned agent ID (agentcube provider)\n571:   - `agent_endpoint`: endpoint URL for invoking agent\n572:   - `deployment_type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` or `\"Deployment\"`\n573:   - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n574:   - `k8s_deployment`: full deployment info dict\n575: \n576: ---\n577: \n578: ### Requirement: Provider Selection Validation\n579: \n580: The system SHALL validate provider selection.\n581: \n582: #### Scenario: Valid Provider Values\n583: \n584: - **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube` or `--provider k8s` is provided\n585: - **WHEN** provider is validated\n586: - **THEN** the system SHALL accept the value and proceed\n587: \n588: #### Scenario: Invalid Provider Value\n589: \n590: - **GIVEN** `--provider helm` is provided\n591: - **WHEN** provider is validated\n592: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating valid providers are `agentcube` and `k8s`\n593: \n594: ---\n595: \n596: ### Requirement: Publish Command Help Text\n597: \n598: The system SHALL provide help text for all publish command options.\n599: \n600: #### Scenario: Publish Command Help Display\n601: \n602: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --help`\n603: - **WHEN** the help is displayed\n604: - **THEN** Typer SHALL show:\n605:   - Command description\n606:   - All options with their names, types, defaults, and help strings\n607:   - Usage examples if configured\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ### Requirement: Workspace Path Resolution\n612: \n613: The system SHALL resolve the workspace path to an absolute path.\n614: \n615: #### Scenario: Resolve Relative Workspace Path\n616: \n617: - **GIVEN** `workspace = \".\"` (relative path)\n618: - **WHEN** the publish command processes the workspace\n619: - **THEN** the system SHALL resolve it to an absolute path using `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Python SDK Integration\n624: \n625: The system SHALL use kubernetes Python client for API interactions.\n626: \n627: #### Scenario: Load Kubeconfig\n628: \n629: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is not specified\n630: - **WHEN** provider initializes\n631: - **THEN** `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` SHALL be called to load from `~/.kube/config`\n632: \n633: #### Scenario: Load Explicit Kubeconfig\n634: \n635: - **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` path is specified\n636: - **WHEN** provider initializes\n637: - **THEN** `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)` SHALL be called\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## Constants Summary\n642: \n643: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n644: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n645: | Default namespace | `\"default\"` | `k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube_provider.py` | Fallback namespace for deployments |\n646: | Default replicas | `1` | `k8s_provider.py` | Default replica count for Deployment |\n647: | Deployment timeout | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Seconds to wait for deployment readiness |\n648: | Poll interval | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Seconds between readiness checks |\n649: | NodePort min | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n650: | NodePort max | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n651: | Session timeout | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime session timeout |\n652: | Max session duration | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime max session duration |\n653: | ImagePullSecret | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default image pull secret name |\n654: | CR API group | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n655: | CR API version | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n656: | CR plural | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n657: \n658: ---\n659: \n660: ## Dependencies Summary\n661: \n662: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n663: |---------|---------|---------|\n664: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n665: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n666: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n667: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n668: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client for Deployment/Service/CR management (optional `[k8s]` dependency) |\n669: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n670: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n671: | `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n672: \n673: ---\n674: \n675: ## File Changes Summary\n676: \n677: | File | Action | Description |\n678: |------|--------|-------------|\n679: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Extend | Add `publish` Typer command with all CLI options |\n680: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Create | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration |\n681: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Create | `KubernetesProvider` for Deployment/Service management |\n682: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Create | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n683: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Extend | Add `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk` methods |\n684: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Extend | Handle `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields |\n685: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Create | Unit tests for PublishRuntime |\n686: | `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | Create | Unit tests for KubernetesProvider |\n687: | `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | Create | Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider |\n688: \n689: ---\n690: \n691: ## References\n692: \n693: - AR-021 — CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n694: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n695: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n696: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n697: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n698: - deployment/spec.md — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n699: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n700: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n701: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n702: \n703: ---\n704: \n705: ## Validation Checklist\n706: \n707: - [ ] Publish command registered in Typer app with correct options\n708: - [ ] Options have correct types and defaults matching spec\n709: - [ ] PublishRuntime orchestrates validation, image prep, deployment, metadata update\n710: - [ ] AgentCube provider validates router_url and workload_manager_url\n711: - [ ] Kubernetes provider creates Deployment and NodePort Service\n712: - [ ] NodePort range validation (30000-32767) implemented\n713: - [ ] wait_for_deployment_ready with 120s timeout implemented\n714: - [ ] AgentRuntime CR created with correct API group/version/plural\n715: - [ ] CR includes sessionTimeout=\"15m\", maxSessionDuration=\"8h\"\n716: - [ ] Image push with Docker SDK and registry credentials\n717: - [ ] Metadata updated with agent_id, agent_endpoint, k8s_deployment\n718: - [ ] Error handling updates metadata before raising\n719: - [ ] Verbose mode enables detailed logging\n720: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during execution\n721: - [ ] Provider selection validation (agentcube/k8s)\n722: - [ ] Namespace support from CLI option or metadata\n723: - [ ] Replicas and NodePort configuration supported\n724: - [ ] Version override via CLI option\n725: - [ ] Unit tests for all components with mocked K8s/Docker APIs\n\n(End of file - total 725 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Publish Command Entry Point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `publish` subcommand via Typer application to deploy agents to Kubernetes with provider selection.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872629165,"end":1775872629206}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872629213,"sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41d945001aEXIP375hnq1jh","messageID":"msg_d7a41b3d5001rjWQMwXaQ58FBA","sessionID":"ses_285be629fffex1IrTiAjm9DBy7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6c2826a904b0401ba70bbe471d613dad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Metadata Model Extensions (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Add `k8s_deployment` field to `AgentMetadata`\n20:   - Type: `Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)`\n21:   - Purpose: Store Kubernetes deployment information\n22:   - Fields: `type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`, `status`, `error`\n23:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n24:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_k8s_deployment_field -v`\n25: \n26: - [ ] **T1.2**: Add `agent_id` field to `AgentMetadata`\n27:   - Type: `str = Field(\"\", description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")`\n28:   - Purpose: Unique identifier assigned by AgentCube provider\n29:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n30:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_id_field -v`\n31: \n32: - [ ] **T1.3**: Add `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` fields\n33:   - `readiness_probe_path: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Path for readiness probe\")`\n34:   - `readiness_probe_port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port for readiness probe\")`\n35:   - Purpose: Configure health check endpoints for AgentRuntime CR\n36:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_readiness_probe_fields -v`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: KubernetesProvider Class (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `k8s_provider.py` skeleton\n42:   - Import: `kubernetes`, `time`, `re`, `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n43:   - Define constants: `NODE_PORT_MIN=30000`, `NODE_PORT_MAX=32767`, `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=120`, `POLL_INTERVAL=2`\n44:   - Define class: `class KubernetesProvider`\n45:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n46:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\"`\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()`\n49:   - Parameters: `namespace: str = \"default\"`, `verbose: bool = False`, `kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None`\n50:   - Load kubeconfig: `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)` or default\n51:   - Initialize APIs: `self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()`, `self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()`\n52:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n53:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_init -v`\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_sanitize_name()` method\n56:   - Convert name to lowercase DNS-compliant (max 63 chars)\n57:   - Pattern: `re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", name.lower())`\n58:   - Truncate to 63 chars, remove leading/trailing `-`\n59:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n60:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_sanitize_name -v`\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n63:   - Check if namespace exists via `self.core_api.read_namespace()`\n64:   - Create if not exists: `self.core_api.create_namespace()`\n65:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n66:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_ensure_namespace -v`\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement `_create_deployment()` method\n69:   - Build Deployment body with: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`\n70:   - Include: `replicas`, `selector`, `template` with container spec\n71:   - Container: `name`, `image`, `ports`, `env` from env_vars\n72:   - Call `self.apps_api.create_namespaced_deployment()`\n73:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n74:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_create_deployment -v`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `_create_service()` method\n77:   - Build NodePort Service body with: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`\n78:   - Type: `NodePort`, selector matching deployment labels\n79:   - Port mapping: `port`, `targetPort`, optional `nodePort`\n80:   - Call `self.core_api.create_namespaced_service()`\n81:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n82:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_create_service -v`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T2.7**: Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` method\n85:   - Poll `self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment()` status\n86:   - Check `deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas`\n87:   - Sleep `POLL_INTERVAL` seconds between checks\n88:   - Raise `TimeoutError` if `timeout` exceeded\n89:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n90:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_wait_for_ready -v`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement `deploy_agent()` main method\n93:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `env_vars`\n94:   - Validate `node_port` in range 30000-32767 if provided\n95:   - Call `_ensure_namespace()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n96:   - Call `_create_deployment()`, `_create_service()`\n97:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n98:   - Return deployment info dict\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n100:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_deploy_agent -v`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T2.9**: Implement `get_agent_status()` method\n103:   - Read Deployment: `self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment()`\n104:   - Read Service: `self.core_api.read_namespaced_service()`\n105:   - Return combined status dict\n106:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n107:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_get_status -v`\n108: \n109: - [ ] **T2.10**: Implement `delete_agent()` method\n110:   - Delete Deployment: `self.apps_api.delete_namespaced_deployment()`\n111:   - Delete Service: `self.core_api.delete_namespaced_service()`\n112:   - Return deletion status dict\n113:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n114:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_delete_agent -v`\n115: \n116: ### Phase 3: AgentCubeProvider Class (ST-3)\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `agentcube_provider.py` skeleton\n119:   - Import: `kubernetes`, `re`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n120:   - Define constants: `CR_GROUP=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `CR_VERSION=\"v1alpha1\"`, `CR_PLURAL=\"agentruntimes\"`\n121:   - Define class: `class AgentCubeProvider`\n122:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n123:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\"`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()`\n126:   - Parameters: `namespace: str = \"default\"`, `verbose: bool = False`, `kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None`\n127:   - Load kubeconfig\n128:   - Initialize APIs: `self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()`, `self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()`\n129:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n130:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_init -v`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `_sanitize_name()` method (reuse pattern from KubernetesProvider)\n133:   - Same DNS-compliant sanitization logic\n134:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n135:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_sanitize_name -v`\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n138:   - Same pattern as KubernetesProvider\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n140:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_ensure_namespace -v`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement `deploy_agent_runtime()` method\n143:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n144:   - Validate required fields: `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n145:   - Build AgentRuntime CR body with spec\n146:   - Call `_ensure_namespace()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n147:   - Try `create_namespaced_custom_object()`, catch 409 → `patch_namespaced_custom_object()`\n148:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n149:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_deploy_agent_runtime -v`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement AgentRuntime CR body template\n152:   - `apiVersion`: `\"{CR_GROUP}/{CR_VERSION}\"`\n153:   - `kind`: `\"AgentRuntime\"`\n154:   - `spec`: `image`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `sessionTimeout=\"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration=\"8h