89:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_login -v`\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T4.4**: Add `get_local_image_url()` method\n192:   - Parameters: `image_name: str`, `tag: str`\n193:   - Check if image exists locally\n194:   - Return full image name with tag\n195:   - Raise error if image not found\n196:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n197:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_get_local_image_url -v`\n198: \n199: ### Phase 5: PublishRuntime Class (ST-5)\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T5.1**: Create `publish_runtime.py` skeleton\n202:   - Import: `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`, `logging`\n203:   - Import services: `MetadataService`, `DockerService`, `KubernetesProvider`, `AgentCubeProvider`\n204:   - Define class: `class PublishRuntime`\n205:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n206:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\"`\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `PublishRuntime.__init__()`\n209:   - Parameters: `verbose: bool = False`, `provider: str = \"agentcube\"`\n210:   - Initialize `self.verbose`, `self.metadata_service`, `self.docker_service`\n211:   - Validate provider: must be `\"agentcube\"` or `\"k8s\"`\n212:   - Initialize appropriate provider: `AgentCubeProvider` or `KubernetesProvider`\n213:   - Raise `ValueError` for invalid provider\n214:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n215:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_init -v`\n216: \n217: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `publish()` main entry method\n218:   - Signature: `publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n219:   - Load metadata via `self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n220:   - Apply CLI option overrides to metadata\n221:   - Call `_prepare_image_for_publishing()`\n222:   - Route to `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` or `_publish_k8s()` based on provider\n223:   - Call `_update_publish_metadata()` on success\n224:   - Return result dict with: `agent_name`, `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `deployment_type`, `namespace`\n225:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n226:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_publish_success -v`\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` method\n229:   - Check `metadata.build_mode`\n230:   - Call `_prepare_local_image()` for `local` mode\n231:   - Call `_prepare_cloud_image()` for `cloud` mode\n232:   - Return image URL string ready for deployment\n233:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n234:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_prepare_image -v`\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `_prepare_local_image()` method\n237:   - Validate `image_url` provided via CLI or metadata\n238:   - Get local image via `docker_service.get_local_image_url()`\n239:   - Tag image if registry_url differs: `docker_service.tag_image()`\n240:   - Login to registry if credentials provided: `docker_service.login()`\n241:   - Push image: `docker_service.push_image()`\n242:   - Return pushed image URL\n243:   - Raise `ValueError` if `image_url` missing\n244:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n245:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_prepare_local_image -v`\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `_prepare_cloud_image()` method\n248:   - Use `metadata.image[\"image_name\"]` with `metadata.registry_url` prefix\n249:   - Build cloud image URL: `f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}:{tag}\"`\n250:   - Return image URL (no push needed for cloud)\n251:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n252:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_prepare_cloud_image -v`\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T5.7**: Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` method\n255:   - Call `self.agentcube_provider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n256:   - Parameters from metadata: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`\n257:   - Validate required: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`\n258:   - Return deployment result with `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`\n259:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n260:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_publish_agentcube -v`\n261: \n262: - [ ] **T5.8**: Implement `_publish_k8s()` method\n263:   - Call `self.k8s_provider.deploy_agent()`\n264:   - Parameters from metadata and options: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`\n265:   - Wait for deployment ready\n266:   - Get `node_port` from Service result\n267:   - Build `service_url`: `f\"http://localhost:{node_port}\"`\n268:   - Return deployment result\n269:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n270:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_publish_k8s -v`\n271: \n272: - [ ] **T5.9**: Implement `_update_publish_metadata()` method\n273:   - Update `metadata.agent_id` from result\n274:   - Update `metadata.agent_endpoint` from result\n275:   - Update `metadata.k8s_deployment` dict with deployment info\n276:   - Call `self.metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n277:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n278:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_update_metadata -v`\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T5.10**: Implement `_apply_option_overrides()` method\n281:   - Override metadata fields from CLI options\n282:   - Fields: `version`, `description`, `region`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`\n283:   - Provider-specific: `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n284:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.p